data.text: The world around her was changing and she smiled knowing that she was part of this change.

Demand and precision didn’t scare her. 
She was sure of what her passion was, and it didn’t hold her back.
She wanted to prove her skills and not to be defined by who she was but by what she could do. And, little by little, she succeeded.

Ambition is the daily impulse for Irene, Type Rating coordinator for Volotea. Discover her story.
#WomenTakeOff #WomensDay https://t.co/1HZ2qvKyWf

data.text:
She discovered that with her strength, she could fly wherever she decided. 
And although the take-off was the most difficult part of the journey, the world awaited. For her and for all the women yet to come.

With flying in her genes, her future was obvious.
Nobody expected more. But they didn’t expect less either. 
Pitying smiles didn’t intimidate her. 
They made her fight every day. They made her learn quickly. They made her be more demanding.

It’ s normal to ask yourself if it is worth it. It’s difficult to keep moving forward like Alice, one of our Volotea pilots, did. Discover her story.
#WomenTakeOff #WomensDay https://t.co/SfuXNts8wg
